heaviest_rainrate.status: The rain rate reached 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

summary.description:
Today, cooler for the feels like temperature (down 3.5°C), outside temperature (down 3.1°C), and inside temperature (down 2.4°C) and more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 6%).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in cloud levels (up 542 m).

The past week and month had observable variation in dew point temperature (up 50.9°C), feels like temperature (up 56.0°C), outside temperature (up 53.3°C), and cloud levels (down 151 m) when compared to today.
